<p><a name="References" id="References"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Gift_economy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Marcel_Mauss" title="Marcel Mauss">Marcel Mauss</a>: <i>The Gift: The Form and Reason for Exchange in Archaic Societies</i>. Originally published as <i>Essai sur le don. Forme et raison de l'échange dans les sociétés archaïques</i> in 1925, modern English edition: <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/039332043X" class="internal">ISBN 0-393-32043-X</a>. Lewis Hyde calls this "the classic work on gift exchange".</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Lewis_Hyde" title="Lewis Hyde">Lewis Hyde</a>: <i>The Gift: Imagination and the Erotic Life of Property</i>, 1983 (<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0394715195" class="internal">ISBN 0-394-71519-5</a>), especially part I, "A Theory of Gifts", part of which was originally published as "The Gift Must Always Move" in <i>Co-Evolution Quarterly</i> No. 35, Fall 1982.</li>
</ul>
