<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Gift_economy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://futurepositive.synearth.net/stories/storyReader$223" class="external text" title="http://futurepositive.synearth.net/stories/storyReader$223" rel="nofollow">Links to numerous gift economy related articles</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.freeebay.net/" class="external text" title="http://www.freeebay.net/" rel="nofollow">Free Gift economy on the internet</a>. An online project, a community of people dedicated to the free gift economy who give each other both real physical and digital gifts and grants.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.gift-economy.com/" class="external text" title="http://www.gift-economy.com/" rel="nofollow">Center for the Study of the Gift Economy</a>, a website strongly expounding the gift economy from a feminist perspective</li>
<li><a href="http://gifteconomy.org.au/" class="external text" title="http://gifteconomy.org.au/" rel="nofollow">The Gift Economy, Anarchism and Strategies for Change</a>, Dr Terry Leahy, Social Sciences, University of Newcastle, Australia</li>
<li><a href="http://www.accesstoinsight.org/lib/authors/thanissaro/economy.html" class="external text" title="http://www.accesstoinsight.org/lib/authors/thanissaro/economy.html" rel="nofollow">The Economy of Gifts</a> by <a href="/wiki/Thanissaro_Bhikkhu" title="Thanissaro Bhikkhu">Thanissaro Bhikkhu</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.thetopdonor.com" class="external text" title="http://www.thetopdonor.com" rel="nofollow">An experiment on public giving</a></li>
<li>[http:www.charitygiftcertificates.org/purchase.asp Charity Gift cards - Direct gift for the economy]</li>
<li><a href="http://www.dematerialism.net/emergypop.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.dematerialism.net/emergypop.htm" rel="nofollow">Emergy and Population in a Natural Economy</a> An <a href="/wiki/Emergy" title="Emergy" class="mw-redirect">emergy</a>-based gift economy is discussed. It is referred to as a <a href="/wiki/Natural_economy" title="Natural economy">natural economy</a> because the energy costs of a monetary system are avoided.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.charityfocus.org/docs/cf-draft1.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.charityfocus.org/docs/cf-draft1.pdf" rel="nofollow">[1]</a>, The Tao of CharityFocus, a discussion of how the Gift Economy relates to nonprofit management.</li>
</ul>
